## Phase 1: Core Engagement — Idea Submission, Comments, Auth & Access Control

**Timeline:** Sprint 1-3 | **Priority:** Critical | **Goal:** Make the portal interactive and configurable

### 1.1 Portal Access Control System (Admin + Backend)

The admin must be able to configure how the public portal is accessed. This is the single most important architectural decision.

#### Admin Configuration (new `board_settings` table)

```
board_settings:
  board_id            TEXT PK REFERENCES boards(id)
  access_mode         TEXT CHECK IN ('public', 'link_only', 'private', 'domain_restricted')
  allowed_domains     TEXT[]         -- e.g. ['company.com', 'partner.org']
  allowed_emails      TEXT[]         -- e.g. ['vip@client.com']  
  require_auth_to_vote       BOOLEAN DEFAULT false
  require_auth_to_comment    BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  require_auth_to_submit     BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  allow_anonymous_ideas      BOOLEAN DEFAULT false
  custom_logo_url     TEXT
  custom_accent_color TEXT
  portal_title        TEXT           -- override board name
  show_vote_count     BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  show_status_filter  BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  show_category_filter BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  enable_idea_submission BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  enable_commenting   BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
  welcome_message     TEXT
  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ
  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ
```

#### Access Mode Behaviors

| Mode | Who Can View | Who Can Vote | Who Can Comment | Who Can Submit |
|------|-------------|-------------|-----------------|----------------|
| `public` | Anyone | Anyone (configurable) | Auth required (configurable) | Auth required (configurable) |
| `link_only` | Anyone with the URL | Auth required | Auth required | Auth required |
| `private` | Authenticated users only | Authenticated users only | Authenticated users only | Auth required |
| `domain_restricted` | Users with email in allowed domains | Same | Same | Same |

#### UI: Admin Board Settings Panel

Add a new "Portal Settings" tab in the admin dashboard ([PortalApp.tsx](file:///Users/ashishnigam/Startups/CustomerVoice/apps/web/src/PortalApp.tsx)) under each board:

```
