### 1.2 Portal User Authentication

#### Backend Changes

**New API routes in [public.ts](file:///Users/ashishnigam/Startups/CustomerVoice/apps/api/src/routes/public.ts):**

```
POST   /public/auth/register        - email + password registration
POST   /public/auth/login           - email + password login
POST   /public/auth/magic-link      - passwordless magic link
GET    /public/auth/me               - get current session
POST   /public/auth/logout           - clear session
```

**New tables:**

```sql
CREATE TABLE portal_users (
  id              TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  email           TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  display_name    TEXT,
  password_hash   TEXT,           -- null if magic-link only
  avatar_url      TEXT,
  auth_provider   TEXT DEFAULT 'email',  -- 'email', 'google', 'github'
  provider_id     TEXT,
  email_verified  BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);

CREATE TABLE portal_sessions (
  id              TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES portal_users(id),
  token           TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  expires_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### UI: Auth Modal

Portal displays a modal when auth is required:

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│        Sign in to CustomerVoice     │
│                                     │
│  Email:    [you@company.com       ] │
│  Password: [••••••••              ] │
│                                     │
│  [Sign In]    or    [Sign Up]       │
│                                     │
│  ──────── or continue with ──────── │
│  [🔵 Google]  [⬛ GitHub]           │
│                                     │
│  [Send Magic Link instead]          │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- Modal appears when user clicks Vote/Comment/Submit and auth is required
- After sign-in, action is immediately performed
- Session persisted via `localStorage` token
- For `domain_restricted` mode, email domain is validated on registration

### 1.3 Idea Submission from Portal

#### Backend Changes

**New API route in [public.ts](file:///Users/ashishnigam/Startups/CustomerVoice/apps/api/src/routes/public.ts):**

```
POST /public/boards/:boardSlug/ideas
Body: { title, description, categoryIds?, authorEmail?, authorName? }
```

- Validates board exists and submission is enabled via `board_settings`
- If auth required, validates portal session token
- If anonymous allowed, creates/uses visitor user
- Returns created idea with auto-status `new`

#### UI: "Submit Idea" Button + Modal

```
┌───── Public Portal Header ─────────────────────────────┐
│  🔵 CustomerVoice | Feature Requests    [🔍 Search...] │
│                                     [+ Submit Idea]     │
