## Phase 3: Platform Excellence — Branding, Changelog, Roadmap, Analytics, Integrations

**Timeline:** Sprint 7-10 | **Priority:** Medium | **Goal:** Premium enterprise-grade portal

### 3.1 Custom Branding & Theming

#### Admin Configuration (extend `board_settings`)
```sql
ALTER TABLE board_settings ADD COLUMN custom_css TEXT;
ALTER TABLE board_settings ADD COLUMN favicon_url TEXT;
ALTER TABLE board_settings ADD COLUMN header_bg_color TEXT;
ALTER TABLE board_settings ADD COLUMN font_family TEXT;
ALTER TABLE board_settings ADD COLUMN hide_powered_by BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;
```

#### UI: Theme Preview in Admin

Live preview panel showing how the portal looks with custom branding.

### 3.2 Public Roadmap View

A new tab or view mode showing a Kanban-style roadmap:

```
┌─── Public Roadmap ──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ [List View]  [🗺 Roadmap View]                                  │
├──────────────┬──────────────┬──────────────┬───────────────────┤
│  📋 Planned  │  ⚡ Building  │  🎉 Shipped  │  ❌ Not Planned   │
│  (12 ideas)  │  (5 ideas)   │  (28 ideas)  │  (3 ideas)       │
├──────────────┼──────────────┼──────────────┼───────────────────┤
│ Dark Mode    │ API v2       │ CSV Export   │ Desktop App      │
│ 142 votes    │ 89 votes     │ 201 votes    │ 15 votes         │
│              │              │              │                   │
│ Webhooks     │ Dashboard    │ SSO Support  │                   │
│ 98 votes     │ Refresh      │ 156 votes    │                   │
│              │ 67 votes     │              │                   │
│ Teams Int.   │              │ Mobile App   │                   │
│ 76 votes     │              │ 134 votes    │                   │
└──────────────┴──────────────┴──────────────┴───────────────────┘
```

### 3.3 Changelog / "What's New"

**New table:**
```sql
CREATE TABLE changelog_entries (
  id              TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  workspace_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES workspaces(id),
  board_id        TEXT REFERENCES boards(id),
  title           TEXT NOT NULL,
  body            TEXT NOT NULL,
  entry_type      TEXT CHECK IN ('feature', 'improvement', 'bugfix', 'announcement'),
  related_idea_ids TEXT[],
  published_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,
  created_by      TEXT REFERENCES users(id),
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

#### UI: Changelog Tab

```
┌─── What's New ──────────────────────────────────────┐
│                                                     │
│  🎉 March 2026                                      │
│  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────  │
│  🟢 FEATURE  Dark Mode Support                      │
│  The most requested feature is here! Enable dark    │
│  mode from Settings > Appearance.                   │
│  → Based on your idea: "Dark Mode" (142 votes)      │
│                                                     │
│  🔵 IMPROVEMENT  Faster Dashboard Loading           │
│  Dashboard now loads 3x faster with optimized       │
│  data fetching.                                     │
│                                                     │
│  🟡 BUGFIX  Fixed CSV export encoding               │
│  CSV exports now properly handle unicode chars.     │
│  → Based on your idea: "Fix CSV" (23 votes)         │
│                                                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 3.4 Email Notifications

**Notification triggers:**
- Status change on followed idea
- Official response on followed idea
- New comment on followed idea
- Idea you submitted gets a milestone (10, 50, 100 votes)
- Weekly digest of top ideas (optional)

Leverages existing `notification_jobs` + `notification_job_recipients` tables.

### 3.5 Comment Threading & Upvotes

Add nested comment replies and comment upvotes:

```sql
ALTER TABLE idea_comments ADD COLUMN parent_comment_id TEXT REFERENCES idea_comments(id);
ALTER TABLE idea_comments ADD COLUMN upvote_count INT DEFAULT 0;

CREATE TABLE comment_upvotes (
  comment_id  TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES idea_comments(id),
  user_id     TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES portal_users(id),
  created_at  TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY(comment_id, user_id)
);
```

### 3.6 Rich Text / Markdown Support

- Idea descriptions and comments support Markdown
- Frontend renders markdown to HTML (use a lightweight lib like `marked`)
- Sanitize HTML on the server side

### 3.7 Embeddable Widget

A small JS widget that can be embedded on any website:

```html
<script src="https://portal.customervoice.com/widget.js" 
        data-board="customervoice-features"
        data-theme="dark"></script>
```

Shows a floating feedback button → opens a mini portal in an iframe.

### 3.8 API Webhooks for Integrations

```sql
CREATE TABLE webhooks (
  id              TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  workspace_id    TEXT NOT NULL REFERENCES workspaces(id),
  url             TEXT NOT NULL,
  events          TEXT[] NOT NULL,  -- ['idea.created', 'idea.voted', 'comment.created']
  secret          TEXT NOT NULL,
  active          BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

Events: `idea.created`, `idea.voted`, `idea.status_changed`, `comment.created`, `idea.subscribed`

### Phase 3 Summary of Changes

#### Database Migrations (`007_platform_excellence`)
- `board_settings` extended columns
- `changelog_entries` table
- Comment threading columns (`parent_comment_id`, `upvote_count`)
- `comment_upvotes` table
- `webhooks` table

#### API Routes
- Changelog CRUD + public listing
- Comment thread endpoints
- Comment upvote endpoints
- Webhook management endpoints
- Widget configuration endpoint

#### Frontend Changes
- Custom branding application
- Public roadmap Kanban view
- Changelog / "What's New" page
- Threaded comments with upvotes
- Markdown rendering
- Embeddable widget iframe

---

## Cross-Cutting Concerns (All Phases)

### Security
- Rate limiting on public endpoints (10 req/min for submissions, 30 for votes)
- CSRF protection for portal auth
- XSS prevention (sanitize all user input, especially markdown)
- SQL injection prevention (parameterized queries — already in place)
- Access mode enforcement at API level (not just UI)

### Performance
- Cache board settings (invalidate on admin update)
- Paginate all list endpoints
- Use database indexes for all query patterns
- Consider CDN for static assets in production

### Analytics (Admin Side)
- Track page views, unique visitors per board
- Funnel: visit → vote → comment → submit
- Top referrers for shared ideas

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests

Each phase should have integration tests covering:

**Phase 1 verification:**
```bash
# Run the API server
cd apps/api && pnpm dev

# Run existing tests (if any)
pnpm test

# Manual browser verification via browser subagent:
# 1. Navigate to http://localhost:3000/portal/boards/customervoice-features
# 2. Verify "Submit Idea" button appears
# 3. Click Submit Idea → verify modal opens
# 4. Verify share button appears on idea cards
# 5. Verify auth modal appears when action requires sign-in
# 6. Verify dynamic filters are rendered
```

**Phase 2 verification:**
```bash
# Browser verification:
# 1. Navigate to idea detail page via /portal/boards/:slug/ideas/:ideaId
# 2. Verify Follow button appears and toggles
# 3. Verify Star/Favorite button works
# 4. Verify user menu appears when signed in
# 5. Verify infinite scroll loads more ideas
# 6. Verify mobile responsive layout at 375px width
```

**Phase 3 verification:**
```bash
# Browser verification:
# 1. Verify custom branding renders correctly
# 2. Navigate to Roadmap view and verify Kanban layout
# 3. Navigate to Changelog and verify entries display
# 4. Verify threaded comments render with reply buttons
# 5. Verify markdown rendering in idea descriptions
```

### Manual Verification
- Admin configures board with each access mode and tests portal behavior
- User tests all auth flows: register → login → vote → comment → submit
- Share functionality tested across Twitter, LinkedIn, email
- Mobile testing on real device or DevTools responsive mode

